From: c878109@idcad7.uucp (Michael Cederberg)
Subject: Re: TAMU X INSTALL
Date: Mon, 22 Nov 1993 15:45:23 GMT

wpp@marie.physik.tu-berlin.de (Kai Petzke) writes:

>>One thing that I would like so see, is a MSDOZE program that could query my
>>card about it's current mode. This way, I'll be able to use the parameters
>>in BIOS which shouldn't burn my card. I realize that not all XFree86 users
>>use MSDOS, but nearly everybody has the ability to boot from an MSDOS-floppy.

>Does windoze boot from a floppy, too?  You want to query your card

Nope, but my ET4000/W32 (and every other ET4000 card I have ever seen) comes
with a program called DMODE, which can be used to set the mode. When I
installed OS/2, it called this program to allow me to set the refresh rate.
After the program terminated, OS/2 read the registers and saved them for 
later use ... 

