From: cherruel@kerroch.univ-brest.fr (Gildas Cherruel)
Subject: DLL under Linux
Date: 22 Nov 1993 12:20:37 GMT

Hi Linuxers,

Does anyone know how to make dll libraries under Linux
(such as lib!@@!.so.#.#)?

If you read the Makefile produced by xmkmf and imake
you can see the following line:

DLLBIN = /usr/dll/bin

and gcc would be called with '-B/usr/dll/bin' but I can't find
this special feature on my disk (neither on nets!).

You can find an example of this in the distribution of
libXpm-3.2.#. The author uses /usr/dll/bin!!!

Help,
Gildas.

